name: 2,5-bis(1-naphthyl)-1,3,4-oxadiazole
Reason: 1,3,4-Oxadiazole ring: The oxadiazole ring introduces additional rigid structures that can participate in dipole interactions and potentially hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by about +70°C. Naphthyl groups: The two naphthyl rings can significantly increase the melting point due to their ability to enhance π-π interactions and overall molecular rigidity. Each naphthyl group may contribute around +30 to +50°C.
